      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera represents the pinnacle of the 996.2 generation, featuring the 3.6L flat-six M96 powerplant with a verified LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit. The naturally aspirated boxer engine delivers linear power through a crisp G96 six-speed manual transaxle. The chassis remains taut, benefitting from original Bilstein dampers and a multi-link rear suspension geometry that ensures surgical turn-in. The exterior maintains its factory luster with zero signs of oxidation, while the underbody is remarkably clean, showing no salt corrosion or fluid seepage. Inside, the cabin boasts supple leather with zero bolster wear, and all switchgear retains factory tactile feedback. Mechanically, the vehicle is turn-key, with recent oil analysis confirming zero bore scoring and optimal wear metals. This is a concours-level example for the discerning collector seeking peak analog performance.",
